  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I'm Miss Maya. I just love how vividly you describe food, that popcorn line was great! What’s your go to snack while watching a Bollywood movie?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks! I usually go for bhel puri or pani puri while watching a movie. But sometimes, I just crack open some popcorn, like you said! Do you watch Bollywood movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Bhel puri with a movie sounds perfect, I can imagine the crunch! Yes, I watch Bollywood for the songs and the drama. What’s one song that makes you feel the movie most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Oh, there's this one song from *Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara* called \"Aashiqui\". It just gives me that movie vibe, you know? The music is so energetic, and it always makes me smile. Do you have a favorite song like that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Aashiqui\" is a great pick, it makes the movie feel even bigger. I love how songs can bring everything to life. What’s one song that makes you feel like dancing?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, dancing... there's this song \"Barish\" from *Street Dancer 3D*. The beat is so catchy, and every time I hear it, I start moving, even if I’m just in my room. My friends say I have two left feet, but I don’t care! What about you, any dance songs?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said it perfectly that time, \"I have two left feet\", and I love the spirit! I’m more of a *Lag Ja Gale* slow sway person, but I get the energy of \"Barish.\" What do you and your friends end up dancing to the most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We mostly groove to old-school songs like \"Mera Naam Lakshmi\" or \"Choli Ke Peeche Kya Hai\" for fun. They’re easy to dance to and always get everyone laughing. But sometimes, we just play random Bollywood mixes—anything with a good beat!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a good mix of fun and laughter. Old songs have a way of bringing people together. What’s your favorite kind of Bollywood music, old or new?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I like the old ones more. The music feels more... soulful, you know? But some new songs are pretty catchy too. Gotta go now, but this was a nice chat!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Old songs do have that soul, and it shows in your words. What’s one new song you think everyone should hear?"
    }
  ],
